Let’s talk real friends and “industry” friends. I’ve had my share of it all. One sided, over possessive, non-loyal friendships. I’ve also connected with some amazing people, but there has been difficulty in connecting with others as I grow in this field. 

I believe the word “friend” is used too loosely these days. If one can’t simply remember my birth date or my favorite food or color, I don’t believe you’ve put in the proper work to becoming a friend. May seem simple but details as such are important…to ME. 😅

Anyone else find building genuine friendships to be a struggle?

Relationships are mirrors. They reveal so much including trauma from all aspects of life. I love that I know how to identify the trauma I’ve endured and often times still internalizing. This comes from years of therapy. 

I’m grateful that I’m aware of my triggers. Now, where I fall short on is my response to these things.  I’m learning..They don’t always require a response, a reaction…but they do require some nurturing, patience and understanding from those who love you and care about you. That’s why relationships with people who are emotionally intelligent, safe and who know how to hold themselves accountable and give YOU room to grow are important. 

In that I find it hard to understand people who look for others to recognize, change, re-work and re-wire themselves as they remain the same. Nearly impossible.

I often think how crazy this posture has saved my life. It’s afforded me opportunities to travel the world. It’s allowed me to employ friends, family and peers. I’m able to meet so many different people with various walks of life. 

It gets hard sometimes, pretty often. I’ve had to start over many times, but it’s been my saving grace. It’s something I’ve been the most proud of. This journey of entrepreneurship has undeniably shaped me as a man. It’s taught me to know my worth and speak up to demand it. To say God favors me is a understatement, his grace and mercy follows my every step especially in the season I’ve been in. I’ve never lacked.

Anytime you get discouraged, frustrated, sad or even depleted, remember your WHY, remember what it took and what it takes for you to be where you are. MAXIMIZE your gift. Run it up, that’s what God wants you to do. He’ll handle the hard stuff. Trust him and then trust yourself! 

📸: @papigordo_

Today makes 14 years on this journey. I’ve learned a lot, still learning. Still growing. God has been SO GOOD to me man. Even when all of these things seem IMPOSSIBLE, God in every step of the way has proved it is when your HEART is in it! 

People always ask for my advice and it’s simple. Consistency, faith and hard work. I’ve been through every step and road block possible in this. Broke, wealthy, broke again. No clients to then a whole roster. Taken advantage of, but then given the advantage! I could go on and on. 

It’s not about money and status for me. It’s about serving people in the capacity God has gifted me. It’s about longevity and impact. It’s about living in YOUR truth and walking in YOUR purpose. This keeps me grounded. 

Thank you to every client old, new and current. Thanks to every business. Let’s keep it going! ❤️

When I think of a selfless person, Courtney is who I think of. My friend is such a pilar of triumph and endurance. She’s faced some situations that would make any one else FOLD but in it she’s always remained positive, optimistic and hopeful. My friend is such a light. I often get upset sometimes that some of the wrong people get to experience her radiance, her beauty, HER PRESENCE but I understand her impact and purpose. If you get to experience her, call yourself BLESSED. Some even envy her because she’s just HER and has been consistent in being so (I be so mad lol) nonetheless, there are a few things my friend has taught me this year. 

One being that evolving is a necessary part of life and doing it for you is what’s important. She’s also taught me that life is to be LIVED and you can do it alone. My friend has supported me beyond imaginable. She’s sponsored events, let me sleep on her couch or even get away at her home. She’s more than what she has done, though. Her spirit is UNMATCHED. 

I’m so grateful for our friendship. Almost 15 years. Courtney, I’m so proud of you. I’m so excited for this new year for you. I’m so excited to witness God’s blessings and favor on your life exceed your expectations.  I decree and declare peace, love, happiness and your hearts desires to meet you where it’s needed. You are loved. Happy Birthday friend. I love you! @itsjustcmo
